{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"833160dd-e062-46c9-93a2-aa224aaecc96","content":"Use `#if` preprocessor directives with MAUI's platform target constants to conditionally register each implementation:\n\n```csharp\n// MauiProgram.cs\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, iOSNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `ANDROID`, `IOS`, and `WINDOWS` are predefined by the MAUI SDK per target framework.\n- Each platform-specific class lives under `Platforms/<Platform>/` by convention (e.g., `Platforms/Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs`).\n- Only the matching implementation is compiled for each platform, so no runtime errors from missing platform APIs.\n- Inject `INotificationService` via constructor injection anywhere in shared code.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f2fa0a28-22b5-4f08-b1a1-14f79cb3dc40","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not tied to any code in the working directory.","outputTokens":357,"requestId":"1032:22188A:1508A1F:17B3217:69FD3631"},"id":"295b20c7-42e1-462b-8b59-4a1035e6b459","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:51.178Z","parentId":"28179b9c-cd1b-44c9-8173-c4d810df1942"}
